From Soup: 68 To derive a plausible form for the coupling between Frenkel and CT excitons we consider again the theory of configuration interaction and assume that the Frenkel excited states | ij 〉 are described by an excited configuration from the HOMO to the LUMO of the molecule in site ( i , j ). If we consider that the Fock matrix elements between non-neighbouring sites are negligible, the only non-zero matrix elements between states | ij 〉 and | ij , kl 〉 involve the Fock matrix element of the LUMO of the donor in site ( i ,1) ( i.e. at the interface) and the LUMO of the acceptor in site ( k = i ,1) ( i.e. also at the interface). Setting this matrix element to the constant V DA the coupling between CT and FE states can be written as:
