From Soup: 70 We set C = 0.96 eV throughout this paper, corresponding to lattice distance L = 5 Å 23 and a relative dielectric constant of ε r = 3, 24,25 i.e. to physically plausible values for the interface between two organic crystals. We set V D = V A in the range 0.02–0.10 eV which is typical for molecules with good electronic coupling. 26,27 In the results section we discuss briefly the more general situation where the coupling along the x and z direction is different.
