From cou.: 100 x
From Soup: 100 Fig. 3b also shows that CT excitons are more bound (more localized) for small coupling V D . If we consider that these states are originating from the interaction between quasi free hole and electron in the donor and acceptor material, larger coupling is associated with lighter effective masses and less localization. Several papers have successfully described the CT interface exciton in this way 10,29,30 focusing mostly on the lowest energy CT states. Our task however is to describe the generation of any CT state from Frenkel excitons.
