From Soup: 118 The Franck–Condon energy dependence dominates over the energy dependence of the effective coupling and the majority of the CT states are formed closer to the maximum of the Franck–Condon factor (shifted to lower energies because of the exponential decrease of the coupling). Essentially all the results presented in this section can be understood in terms of the contrasting energy dependence of the two functions V 2 ( E ) and F ( E ) that contribute to the charge separation rate.
